title: Walnut-Crusted Salmon Sticks and Dill-icious Dip
directions: Whisk together dip ingredients in a medium bowl and refrigerate.
In a food processor, combine walnuts, panko, salt and pepper and pulse until breadcrumb consistency. Transfer to a plate.
In a shallow bowl, beat egg whites until frothy. add lemon juice and stir to combine.

Cut salmon fillet into 1/2-inch strips to make 20 fish sticks. Dip one strip into egg mixture, letting excess drip off, and then into walnut mixture, pressing to adhere. repeat with remaining salmon strips.

Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add 10 pieces of coated salmon and cook 7 to 8 minutes, flipping halfway through. (Cook in 2 batches to avoid crowding the pan, wiping out the pan before using another 2 tablespoons oil for the second batch.) Serve with dip.
ingredients: 1 pound (16 ounces) wild Pacific skinless salmon fillets
4 tablespoons olive oil or high-heat oil (safflower oil), divided
